  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large pot, sauté the chopped onion, carrot, and celery in olive oil until tender.",
    "Add the borlotti beans, garlic, nutmeg, salt, and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "Top with feta cheese, bread crumbs, and fresh parsley.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the beans are heated through.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!"
